---
import Layout from '@/components/chrome/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Disclosures — The STR Ledger"
  description="Affiliate, advertising, and editorial disclosures for thestrledger.com."
  path="/disclosures"
>
  <section class="bg-parchment">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 pt-12 pb-9">
      <p class="label text-gold-deep">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-serif text-h1 text-navy leading-tight">
        Disclosures<span class="period-gold">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lead text-ink-2">
        Where we make money, where we don't, and what that means for what you read.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-parchment-light border-t border-rule">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-9 prose">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-navy">Revenue</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-body text-ink-2 leading-snug">
        Workbook sales and PDF guides are the primary revenue. The free sister sites (strhost.tools, strbuyers.tools, strops.tools, strguests.tools) may run ads and affiliate links; thestrledger.com generally does not.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-7 font-serif text-h2 text-navy">Affiliate links</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-body text-ink-2 leading-snug">
        Blog posts may include affiliate links to tools we actually use (e.g., dynamic pricing services, hosting platforms). When they do, we mark them with "(affiliate)" inline. Affiliate revenue does not change which tools we recommend.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-7 font-serif text-h2 text-navy">Editorial independence</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-body text-ink-2 leading-snug">
        We do not run sponsored posts. We don't take payment for placement. If a competitor is the right answer, we say so.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-7 text-caption text-ink-3 italic">
        This stub is a placeholder. Full disclosures policy in development.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
